article.headline: Virginia Commonwealth 75, Drexel 68
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP)-B.A. Walker scored 24 points to lift Virginia Commonwealth to its ninth straight win, a 75-68 decision over Drexel on Saturday. Walker scored 19 of his points in the second half, including 11 in the game's final 4:35 to help put the game away for the Rams (18-3, 10-0 Colonial Athletic Association). Eric Maynor added 17 points and Jesse Pellot-Rosa chipped in with 14. The Dragons (7-3, 15-5) were led by Bashir Mason with 19 points. Scott Rodgers added 17 and Chaz Crawford had six blocks for the Dragons. Drexel was without the services of leading scorer Frank Elegar, who served a 1-game suspension by the CAA for unsportsmanlike conduct in the team's Jan. 20 win at Delaware. Randy Oveneke, who started in place of Elegar and finished with 11 points, scored the final four points of the first half and the first three of the second half to give Drexel its biggest lead, 34-29 with 18:42 remaining. Oveneke's dunk off of a miss by Dominick Mejia as time expired in the first half gave the Dragons a 31-29 halftime lead.
